1
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:15,233
<i> Are you almost here?</i>

2
00:00:15,367 --> 00:00:16,233
<i> Hurry up!</i>

3
00:00:16,367 --> 00:00:17,800
<i> Hey!</i>

4
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:21,667
<i>Manuel, I'm on the second floor!</i>

5
00:00:21,800 --> 00:00:24,267
<i>All units, stand by.
Target acquired.</i>

6
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:33,967
<i> Why are there cops here?</i>

7
00:00:34,133 --> 00:00:35,467
<i> My husband called them!</i>

8
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:37,600
<i>They're here to save me.
So let me go!</i>

9
00:00:37,733 --> 00:00:40,667
<i>I won't! As long as I have you,
they can't do anything!</i>

10
00:00:42,133 --> 00:00:44,600
<i>Meet Police Captain
Antonette Ferrer.</i>

11
00:00:44,733 --> 00:00:46,033
<i> Lead Negotiations Officer.</i>

12
00:00:46,167 --> 00:00:47,633
<i>She's a solid,
excellent negotiator.</i>

13
00:00:47,767 --> 00:00:49,367
<i> She has a high success rate.</i>

14
00:00:49,500 --> 00:00:50,833
<i> Snake cam is in.</i>

15
00:00:52,700 --> 00:00:54,633
<i> What's the room number again?</i>

16
00:00:54,767 --> 00:00:55,633
<i> Who's this?</i>

17
00:00:55,767 --> 00:00:57,400
<i> Tell me.</i>

18
00:00:57,533 --> 00:00:58,933
<i>- What do you need?
- Nothing.</i>

19
00:00:59,067 --> 00:01:00,867
<i>I don't need anything.
I already have what I need.</i>

20
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:01,967
<i> What I need is right here.</i>

21
00:01:02,100 --> 00:01:04,767
<i>Will the pain disappear
if you kill Felma?</i>

22
00:01:04,900 --> 00:01:08,267
<i>Yes, because Manuel will mourn
for the rest of his life.</i>

23
00:01:08,433 --> 00:01:10,300
<i>You monsters!
Are you watching me?</i>

24
00:01:10,433 --> 00:01:11,700
<i> Delta, withdraw the optic!</i>

25
00:01:11,833 --> 00:01:13,133
<i> Help me get out of here.</i>

26
00:01:13,267 --> 00:01:15,500
<i>But you need to pay me
ten million first.</i>

27
00:01:15,633 --> 00:01:16,567
<i> Hello, Hazel?</i>

28
00:01:16,700 --> 00:01:17,567
<i> Listen to me.</i>

29
00:01:17,700 --> 00:01:19,800
<i> I need a helicopter.</i>

30
00:01:19,933 --> 00:01:23,033
<i> And I want 20 million pesos.</i>

31
00:01:23,167 --> 00:01:28,167
<i>Okay, do you need anything else
while we work on your demands?</i>

32
00:01:28,300 --> 00:01:30,200
<i> Food? Water?</i>

33
00:01:30,333 --> 00:01:35,667
<i>If you want reassurance,
let Felma eat first.</i>

34
00:01:35,800 --> 00:01:37,133
<i> Fine.</i>

35
00:01:37,267 --> 00:01:38,700
<i> Ready for overwatch, Sir.</i>

36
00:01:54,333 --> 00:01:56,033
Ma'am Felma.

37
00:01:56,167 --> 00:01:58,167
Oh my god, oh my god!

38
00:01:58,300 --> 00:02:00,667
You little monster, Hazel.
You're sneaky.

39
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:02,267
Too damn smart
for your own good.

40
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:05,000
You're a devil, Hazel.
A real devil!

41
00:02:05,133 --> 00:02:06,433
Hazel!

42
00:02:09,433 --> 00:02:10,700
What?

43
00:02:10,833 --> 00:02:13,100
You thought I'd just walk
straight into you, huh?

44
00:02:13,233 --> 00:02:14,867
<i>What do you think I am, stupid?</i>

45
00:02:15,033 --> 00:02:16,633
<i> Give the food to Felma.</i>

46
00:02:16,767 --> 00:02:18,167
<i> Hurry up!</i>

47
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:21,433
Ma'am, be careful.

48
00:02:21,567 --> 00:02:23,300
You think I don't know?

49
00:02:23,433 --> 00:02:26,100
You brought cops with you.
You've got people with you!

50
00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:28,800
Go on. Leave!

51
00:02:32,767 --> 00:02:35,200
Command, this is Bravo 07.
Come in.

52
00:02:36,333 --> 00:02:37,700
Bravo 07. Go ahead.

53
00:02:39,267 --> 00:02:41,800
Felma was the one
who received the food, Sir.

54
00:02:41,933 --> 00:02:44,633
Negative engagement on target
due to hostage proximity.

55
00:02:44,767 --> 00:02:46,533
Requesting further instruction.

56
00:02:48,567 --> 00:02:50,833
Copy. Resume original mission.

57
00:02:52,167 --> 00:02:53,500
Copy. Over and out.

58
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:56,400
Men, standby for orders.

59
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:01,400
Wait. Stay right there.

60
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:09,933
Hurry up.

61
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,033
Come on.

62
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:20,633
Eat.

63
00:03:25,833 --> 00:03:27,667
You're a monster, Hazel!

64
00:03:37,667 --> 00:03:39,133
Please help my mother.

65
00:04:09,433 --> 00:04:10,433
Hey!

66
00:04:13,233 --> 00:04:14,567
Hey! Get back here!

67
00:04:17,633 --> 00:04:18,700
Faster!

68
00:04:31,833 --> 00:04:34,033
Give it to me.
Give it to me.

69
00:04:41,167 --> 00:04:42,900
You need your strength.

70
00:04:44,267 --> 00:04:46,533
So you can fight that demon.

71
00:04:53,767 --> 00:04:55,433
Hey.

72
00:04:55,567 --> 00:04:58,600
Look at yourself.
You look starved.

73
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:05,800
Felma, where are your manners?
So rude.

74
00:05:05,933 --> 00:05:07,800
Don't talk with your mouth full!

75
00:05:07,933 --> 00:05:09,300
What are you muttering about?

76
00:05:12,833 --> 00:05:13,900
Nothing.

77
00:05:14,033 --> 00:05:15,333
I said...

78
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:18,067
I'm really hungry.

79
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:20,800
Not "starved," okay?

80
00:05:20,933 --> 00:05:22,300
I haven't eaten all day.

81
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:26,600
I was busy, remember?

82
00:05:26,733 --> 00:05:28,533
At my wedding with Manuel.

83
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:31,567
The wedding you ruined.

84
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:35,900
You know what...

85
00:05:36,067 --> 00:05:37,933
that wedding ring
you're wearing?

86
00:05:39,933 --> 00:05:41,300
It doesn't suit you.

87
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:44,233
That should be mine!

88
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:46,733
What do you mean
it doesn't suit me?

89
00:05:47,867 --> 00:05:50,100
You were there,
weren't you?

90
00:05:50,233 --> 00:05:54,433
You heard Manuel's vows
before he put this ring on me!

91
00:05:56,633 --> 00:05:57,967
<i> Felma, my love.</i>

92
00:05:58,100 --> 00:05:59,400
<i> First of all,</i>

93
00:05:59,533 --> 00:06:03,500
<i>I want to apologize for
everything I failed to give you.</i>

94
00:06:05,133 --> 00:06:07,967
<i> For all the ways I hurt you.</i>

95
00:06:08,133 --> 00:06:09,133
<i> And...</i>

96
00:06:11,467 --> 00:06:13,367
<i>for every time I neglected you.</i>

97
00:06:15,933 --> 00:06:18,333
<i> For every time...</i>

98
00:06:18,467 --> 00:06:19,767
<i> I caused you pain.</i>

99
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:24,167
<i> My love, you are my world.</i>

100
00:06:26,533 --> 00:06:27,933
<i> You are my home.</i>

101
00:06:30,967 --> 00:06:32,633
<i> You are...</i>

102
00:06:32,767 --> 00:06:34,500
<i> my rest when I'm tired.</i>

103
00:06:36,267 --> 00:06:38,800
<i> You are my smile when I'm sad.</i>

104
00:06:38,933 --> 00:06:41,100
<i>You are the one
I choose and...</i>

105
00:06:42,733 --> 00:06:44,433
<i> love you, today and every day.</i>

106
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:47,567
<i> You were my choice then,</i>

107
00:06:47,700 --> 00:06:50,233
<i>you're my choice now, and you'll
still be my choice tomorrow.</i>

108
00:06:51,667 --> 00:06:53,800
<i>I will love you
every single day.</i>

109
00:06:53,933 --> 00:06:56,467
<i>Even if I die,
I'll still love you.</i>

110
00:06:58,233 --> 00:07:03,233
<i>Even if we cross
into the next life,</i>

111
00:07:03,367 --> 00:07:06,767
<i>I'll find you.
I'll love you again.</i>

112
00:07:08,933 --> 00:07:10,733
<i> And I'll marry you again.</i>

113
00:07:30,500 --> 00:07:31,833
No!

114
00:07:33,167 --> 00:07:35,333
He was supposed to say all
that to me, not to you!

115
00:07:37,500 --> 00:07:39,267
Because I'm the real Mrs. Cruz!

116
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:44,333
Stop living in your fantasy.

117
00:07:44,467 --> 00:07:47,000
You're pathetic.

118
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:50,600
I don't need your pity,
you animal!

119
00:07:52,167 --> 00:07:53,000
- Give that to me!
- This is mine!

120
00:07:53,133 --> 00:07:54,233
Give it to me!

121
00:07:56,433 --> 00:07:57,633
- Give it to me!
- That belongs to me!

122
00:07:57,767 --> 00:07:58,733
Give it to me!

123
00:07:58,867 --> 00:08:01,700
- That should be mine!
- It's mine, Hazel!

124
00:08:01,833 --> 00:08:04,033
I'll shove this
down your throat!

125
00:08:20,733 --> 00:08:21,667
There.

126
00:08:23,933 --> 00:08:25,733
I'm Mrs. Cruz again.

127
00:08:26,867 --> 00:08:28,600
Give it back to me!

128
00:08:31,967 --> 00:08:34,300
Go ahead! Try coming any closer.

129
00:08:34,433 --> 00:08:36,133
I'm not giving
anything back to you.

130
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,567
Because this is mine.

131
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:41,400
This was always meant for me.

132
00:08:41,533 --> 00:08:43,100
This belongs to me.

133
00:08:43,233 --> 00:08:45,200
It always has.

134
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:48,067
Did you forget?

135
00:08:49,900 --> 00:08:52,067
I was first.

136
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:53,867
I'm the real one.

137
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:56,733
The one and only Mrs. Cruz.

138
00:09:03,067 --> 00:09:04,567
It's mine.

139
00:09:04,700 --> 00:09:05,600
See?

140
00:09:05,733 --> 00:09:06,333
Mine.

141
00:09:10,633 --> 00:09:12,500
Suspect is highly mobile.

142
00:09:12,633 --> 00:09:15,133
- No clean angle.
- Hold your position.

143
00:09:15,267 --> 00:09:17,033
Do not fire unless I say so.

144
00:09:17,167 --> 00:09:19,567
Any move now
puts the hostage at risk.

145
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:21,533
Roger. Holding.

146
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:26,967
Come out of there!

147
00:09:29,300 --> 00:09:30,767
I know you're in there.
Come out!

148
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:33,100
Come out!

149
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:41,233
You're the reason
Hazel got away, right?

150
00:09:42,267 --> 00:09:44,033
Now my mom's life is in danger!

151
00:09:59,667 --> 00:10:01,400
Do you want to die
before your mother does?

152
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,100
Uncle Noah.

153
00:10:10,233 --> 00:10:11,233
Uncle Abel.

154
00:10:13,633 --> 00:10:17,000
We saw you chasing this guy,
so we followed you.

155
00:10:18,033 --> 00:10:20,067
Darn it, kid.
You even got into a fistfight.

156
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:21,267
- Who is this guy?
- Yeah, who is he?

157
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:24,467
He's Hazel's accomplice,
who hasn't been caught yet.

158
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:26,767
What? Is that so?

159
00:10:30,233 --> 00:10:31,767
Abel! Abel, stop it!
That's enough!

160
00:10:31,900 --> 00:10:33,500
Stop! Stop!

161
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:35,267
Don't hurt him!

162
00:10:35,433 --> 00:10:36,800
Come here. Come here.

163
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:42,067
I stepped aside

164
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:46,900
so Felma could be happy
with Manuel and their kids.

165
00:10:47,033 --> 00:10:49,567
Not so you and Hazel
could hurt them!

166
00:10:49,700 --> 00:10:51,267
You devils!

167
00:10:52,300 --> 00:10:54,133
You animals!

168
00:11:25,900 --> 00:11:27,200
Look at that.

169
00:11:27,333 --> 00:11:28,867
Hazel seems to have completely
lost it.

170
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:32,033
She's going to hurt Ma'am Felma
with that kind of craziness.

171
00:11:32,167 --> 00:11:34,533
I know it.
She's going to hurt her!

172
00:11:34,667 --> 00:11:37,100
Look! Look!

173
00:11:37,233 --> 00:11:39,267
Ma'am Felma!

174
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:40,767
Ma'am!

175
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:47,400
Eagle Eye, this is Command.
Status.

176
00:11:48,433 --> 00:11:50,133
<i> Negative shot, Sir.</i>

177
00:11:50,267 --> 00:11:52,500
Suspect keeps moving
in and out of frame.

178
00:11:52,633 --> 00:11:54,300
No safe angle.

179
00:11:54,433 --> 00:11:56,667
Copy. Hold fire.

180
00:11:56,800 --> 00:12:00,333
If we miss,
she'll know she's been targeted.

181
00:12:00,467 --> 00:12:02,200
Too risky for the hostage.

182
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,400
Holding.

183
00:12:06,667 --> 00:12:08,100
- Stay right there!
- Jeff.

184
00:12:08,233 --> 00:12:09,400
Abel.

185
00:12:09,533 --> 00:12:10,733
What did you do?
And who is this guy?

186
00:12:10,867 --> 00:12:12,533
Dad, he's Hazel's accomplice.

187
00:12:12,667 --> 00:12:13,567
He helped kidnap me.

188
00:12:13,700 --> 00:12:15,733
He's the one
who helped Hazel escape.

189
00:12:15,900 --> 00:12:18,767
- You bastard! You animal!
- Enough! Enough!

190
00:12:18,900 --> 00:12:20,367
You animal!

191
00:12:20,500 --> 00:12:22,133
- You demon!
- Andrea, stop it!

192
00:12:22,267 --> 00:12:24,833
- Enough!
- Why did you side with Hazel?

193
00:12:24,967 --> 00:12:26,667
How much did she pay you?

194
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:28,533
What's the price
of your conscience?

195
00:12:28,667 --> 00:12:30,233
Or do you not have one
because you're both monsters?

196
00:12:30,367 --> 00:12:31,567
You're both shameless!

197
00:12:31,700 --> 00:12:34,567
- Enough! Enough!
- Monster!

198
00:12:34,700 --> 00:12:36,533
Enough!

199
00:12:36,667 --> 00:12:38,267
Manuel, what is this?

200
00:12:39,333 --> 00:12:41,200
He's Hazel's accomplice.

201
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:48,467
Quiet. Quiet.

202
00:12:48,633 --> 00:12:49,600
Hazel's calling.

203
00:12:55,133 --> 00:12:57,167
Well?

204
00:12:57,300 --> 00:12:58,967
<i> What's taking so long?</i>

205
00:12:59,100 --> 00:13:02,200
Where's the helicopter?
Where's my 20 million pesos?

206
00:13:03,633 --> 00:13:06,000
We're working on it, Hazel.

207
00:13:06,133 --> 00:13:09,300
We have six million so far,
we're still raising the rest.

208
00:13:09,433 --> 00:13:11,500
As for the helicopter,

209
00:13:11,633 --> 00:13:13,767
there's no helipad
inside the resort.

210
00:13:13,900 --> 00:13:17,133
We'll land it at the plaza
and bring you there.

211
00:13:17,267 --> 00:13:20,267
No! That's not what I want!

212
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:23,033
Didn't I say I want it here?
Here!

213
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:25,033
Hazel, that's impossible.

214
00:13:25,167 --> 00:13:27,233
I don't care!
Make it happen!

215
00:13:27,367 --> 00:13:29,500
Now! Hurry up!

216
00:13:29,633 --> 00:13:32,633
Okay, okay.
We'll explore all options.

217
00:13:32,767 --> 00:13:34,600
You'll get what you want.

218
00:13:34,733 --> 00:13:37,500
Just don't hurt Felma, please.

219
00:13:37,633 --> 00:13:39,733
Hazel, don't believe her!

220
00:13:39,867 --> 00:13:41,533
I know her. She's lying!

221
00:13:41,667 --> 00:13:43,667
There is no helicopter!
There is no 20 million!

222
00:13:43,800 --> 00:13:46,100
Get him out of here!
Get him out!

223
00:13:48,333 --> 00:13:50,133
Hazel, don't listen to him.

224
00:13:50,267 --> 00:13:51,400
<i> Don't believe him.</i>

225
00:13:51,533 --> 00:13:54,000
You liars! You played me!

226
00:13:55,067 --> 00:13:56,800
Hazel, listen to me.

227
00:13:56,933 --> 00:13:59,000
What he's saying isn't true.

228
00:13:59,133 --> 00:14:00,400
Don't listen to him.

229
00:14:00,533 --> 00:14:02,000
We've already put
in the request.

230
00:14:02,133 --> 00:14:03,600
You're all trash!

231
00:14:03,733 --> 00:14:06,133
Put it on speaker.
Put it on speaker!

232
00:14:06,267 --> 00:14:07,367
You're on speaker.

233
00:14:08,433 --> 00:14:09,600
Hazel wants you to hear this.

234
00:14:09,733 --> 00:14:11,533
This is what you get
for lying to me.

235
00:14:11,667 --> 00:14:13,367
Listen!

236
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:14,733
- Hazel, don't!
- You monster!

237
00:14:14,867 --> 00:14:17,800
- Hazel!
- Hazel! Stop!

238
00:14:17,933 --> 00:14:19,800
Don't hurt Felma!

239
00:14:21,633 --> 00:14:23,733
That's enough, please!
Have mercy!

240
00:14:23,867 --> 00:14:26,867
- You animal! Animal!
- Stop it, please! Stop!

241
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:28,300
You bastards!

242
00:14:30,033 --> 00:14:32,100
Please, stop! Have mercy!

243
00:14:32,233 --> 00:14:34,700
Leave my mother alone! Stop!

244
00:14:34,833 --> 00:14:36,300
I'm not done yet!

245
00:14:36,433 --> 00:14:38,600
Listen to how
I make this woman suffer,

246
00:14:38,733 --> 00:14:40,167
you pieces of trash!

247
00:14:40,300 --> 00:14:41,100
You animal!

248
00:15:05,333 --> 00:15:07,467
What is this?
Aren't we going to do anything?

249
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:09,633
She's beating our mom!

250
00:15:09,767 --> 00:15:11,567
Get your people moving, Sir!

251
00:15:11,700 --> 00:15:14,033
Please, I'm begging you!

252
00:15:18,367 --> 00:15:19,667
Colonel.

253
00:15:21,233 --> 00:15:23,000
Please breach Room 206.

254
00:15:25,133 --> 00:15:28,000
Colonel, let me go in. Please.

255
00:15:28,133 --> 00:15:29,600
My wife needs me!

256
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:34,267
Hazel needs Felma alive
as leverage.

257
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:37,033
If we go in, that changes.

258
00:15:38,867 --> 00:15:40,367
Let's wait for her to calm down.

259
00:15:40,500 --> 00:15:42,800
I'll talk to her again.

260
00:15:42,933 --> 00:15:45,033
Captain, she won't
believe you anymore.

261
00:15:45,167 --> 00:15:46,400
She won't calm down!

262
00:15:46,533 --> 00:15:49,600
I'll earn her trust again.
That's my job.

263
00:16:05,300 --> 00:16:07,867
Eagle Eye,
do you have a clear shot?

264
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:09,833
Target and hostage
are too close.

265
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:11,433
<i> No safe angle.</i>

266
00:16:11,567 --> 00:16:13,333
Copy. Hold fire.

267
00:16:14,767 --> 00:16:16,900
Sir, the hostage
is fighting back.

268
00:16:17,033 --> 00:16:18,333
What?

269
00:16:26,133 --> 00:16:28,267
I don't know
how to throw a punch.

270
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:29,267
But this.

271
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:31,233
This is what I can do!

272
00:16:34,167 --> 00:16:35,133
That's it!

273
00:16:35,267 --> 00:16:36,567
That's it! Come on, Mom.
Fight back!

274
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:43,700
Keep going, sis! Fight!

275
00:16:47,167 --> 00:16:49,700
There! Beat that devil!

276
00:16:52,500 --> 00:16:53,700
That's my wife.

277
00:16:53,833 --> 00:16:54,700
Come on, love! Fight!

278
00:16:54,833 --> 00:16:56,467
Mom, slap her! Slap her again!

279
00:17:00,367 --> 00:17:01,833
Come on, Mom!
Push her!

280
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:08,467
Mom, keep going!

281
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:11,367
- Keep going! Come on, love!
- Go, Ma'am! Don't stop!

282
00:17:11,500 --> 00:17:13,600
Men, prepare to engage.

283
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:22,233
You shameless witch!

284
00:17:23,333 --> 00:17:24,700
Ma'am!

285
00:17:24,833 --> 00:17:26,200
Be careful, Ma'am!

286
00:17:26,333 --> 00:17:27,633
Colonel.

287
00:17:27,767 --> 00:17:29,733
Colonel,
aren't we going to do anything?

288
00:17:29,867 --> 00:17:31,267
Colonel, wait.

289
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:33,467
- Stay there, Dad.
- Don't.

290
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:35,433
Colonel Sarabia
already told you.

291
00:17:35,567 --> 00:17:36,633
But my wife needs me!

292
00:17:36,767 --> 00:17:37,733
You'll just make things
worse, man.

293
00:17:37,867 --> 00:17:39,167
Don't! Don't!

294
00:17:39,300 --> 00:17:41,833
Men, control the entry.
Move! Move!

295
00:17:43,800 --> 00:17:47,233
Command, I have a possible
shot at the suspect.

296
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:51,600
Confirm.
Is the lane clear?

297
00:17:57,667 --> 00:17:59,467
<i> Suspect is moving.</i>

298
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:01,167
I can track her.

299
00:18:01,300 --> 00:18:03,033
<i> But separation is minimal.</i>

300
00:18:06,867 --> 00:18:07,733
Move! Move!

301
00:18:07,867 --> 00:18:08,767
Mayor.

302
00:18:08,900 --> 00:18:10,667
Mayor! Mayor!

303
00:18:13,033 --> 00:18:14,700
Any designated safe zones?

304
00:18:14,833 --> 00:18:16,567
<i> Negative.</i>

305
00:18:16,700 --> 00:18:18,867
Only viable shot is cranial.

306
00:18:26,933 --> 00:18:29,833
<i> Command, awaiting decision.</i>

307
00:18:31,300 --> 00:18:32,533
Sir, please hold.

308
00:18:32,667 --> 00:18:34,900
The suspect and the hostage
are still entangled.

309
00:18:35,033 --> 00:18:36,833
Felma could get hit.

310
00:18:36,967 --> 00:18:40,367
We're trying to save her,
but she's compromised!

311
00:18:40,500 --> 00:18:43,400
Colonel, my wife could get hit!

312
00:18:43,533 --> 00:18:45,600
Eagle Eye's an expert.

313
00:18:45,733 --> 00:18:47,100
He doesn't miss.

314
00:18:47,233 --> 00:18:49,400
Sir, you heard him.
It's a headshot.

315
00:18:49,533 --> 00:18:51,267
We can't just kill her.

316
00:18:53,167 --> 00:18:54,433
If Hazel dies,

317
00:18:56,200 --> 00:18:57,933
she has no one to blame
but herself.

318
00:18:59,233 --> 00:19:00,467
Captain Ferrer,

319
00:19:02,533 --> 00:19:03,500
she's a criminal.

320
00:19:04,867 --> 00:19:06,200
She's a fugitive.

321
00:19:06,333 --> 00:19:08,067
Sir, we're not disputing that.

322
00:19:09,333 --> 00:19:11,533
But the hostage is our priority.

323
00:19:11,667 --> 00:19:13,533
And neutralization comes second.

324
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:16,767
Sir, please, let me re-engage.

325
00:19:16,900 --> 00:19:18,500
I'll call Hazel again.

326
00:19:23,367 --> 00:19:25,667
You're trapped!
There's nowhere for you to go!

327
00:19:27,233 --> 00:19:29,000
I'm not dying!

328
00:19:29,167 --> 00:19:30,667
Not today, Hazel!

329
00:19:30,800 --> 00:19:32,267
And not because of you!

330
00:19:32,400 --> 00:19:33,433
No!

331
00:19:36,433 --> 00:19:37,533
No!

332
00:19:37,667 --> 00:19:38,767
I'll kill you!

333
00:19:38,900 --> 00:19:41,067
- Die!
- Hazel Capistrano!

334
00:19:49,267 --> 00:19:55,000
This is Mayor Hermie Constancio,
at your service.

335
00:19:55,133 --> 00:19:57,267
May we talk?

336
00:20:09,567 --> 00:20:10,833
Who's that?

337
00:20:14,100 --> 00:20:17,500
Hazel, may I call you?

338
00:20:18,300 --> 00:20:20,233
Let's talk.

339
00:20:20,367 --> 00:20:22,667
Let's fix this.

340
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:26,733
We can settle this calmly,
Hazel.

341
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:28,800
Please.

342
00:20:39,800 --> 00:20:43,100
Mayor, Ma'am,
with all due respect,

343
00:20:43,233 --> 00:20:44,933
this is a police operation.

344
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:49,200
But this is my town.

345
00:20:50,500 --> 00:20:54,867
And it's my responsibility
to keep peace and order.

346
00:20:57,033 --> 00:20:59,033
Hey, everyone.

347
00:20:59,167 --> 00:21:00,933
Like my secretary said,

348
00:21:01,067 --> 00:21:06,433
I promise we'll resolve
this problem peacefully.

349
00:21:08,133 --> 00:21:13,100
I've been serving this town
for eight years.

350
00:21:14,433 --> 00:21:18,467
This town is my home.

351
00:21:18,600 --> 00:21:20,800
As a mother,

352
00:21:22,533 --> 00:21:25,000
I take care
of my children's problems

353
00:21:25,133 --> 00:21:28,167
and make things right.

354
00:21:28,300 --> 00:21:30,933
My constituents know that.

355
00:21:31,067 --> 00:21:33,500
That's why this town
is peaceful. Right?

356
00:21:33,633 --> 00:21:35,233
You all know that.

357
00:21:35,367 --> 00:21:38,733
Mayor, could you please
stop campaigning for a moment?

358
00:21:42,567 --> 00:21:44,400
Don't talk to me like that.

359
00:21:44,533 --> 00:21:49,133
Don't forget you're on my turf.

360
00:21:49,267 --> 00:21:50,467
Enough, please.

361
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:51,800
My wife's life is at risk.

362
00:21:51,933 --> 00:21:53,533
That's what we should focus on!

363
00:21:53,667 --> 00:21:54,767
Please, stop arguing.

364
00:21:54,900 --> 00:21:57,700
Put my mother first.
Save her!

365
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:03,533
Mayor, we all have the same
goal here.

366
00:22:03,667 --> 00:22:06,700
To end this peacefully.
So please, let's work together.

367
00:22:08,067 --> 00:22:11,300
I could use your help
with the negotiation.

368
00:22:11,433 --> 00:22:13,900
But first,
get the press out of here.

369
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:55,500
You should be thankful the Mayor
wants to talk to me.

370
00:22:55,633 --> 00:22:57,500
Otherwise,
you'd already be dead.

371
00:22:57,633 --> 00:23:01,467
Manuel and your kids should've
been mourning you by now!

372
00:23:18,733 --> 00:23:20,367
Hello.

373
00:23:20,500 --> 00:23:22,267
<i> Hazel.</i>

374
00:23:22,433 --> 00:23:24,600
Same demands, Mayor.

375
00:23:24,733 --> 00:23:27,900
A helicopter
and 20 million pesos.

376
00:23:28,033 --> 00:23:30,600
What those cops
failed to deliver.

377
00:23:30,733 --> 00:23:32,367
Yes.

378
00:23:32,500 --> 00:23:33,933
I'm working on it.

379
00:23:34,067 --> 00:23:39,500
My secretary already spoke
to my congressman father-in-law.

380
00:23:39,633 --> 00:23:44,700
I'll borrow the remaining funds
from his latest project.

381
00:23:44,833 --> 00:23:46,633
You know what he told me?

382
00:23:46,767 --> 00:23:50,433
He's got cash in his basement.

383
00:23:51,467 --> 00:23:54,600
I also talked
to my contractor friend,

384
00:23:54,733 --> 00:23:57,533
the one handling
the road widening.

385
00:23:57,700 --> 00:24:02,967
He said he'll lend us
his helicopter.

386
00:24:03,100 --> 00:24:04,533
No. That's too slow.

387
00:24:04,667 --> 00:24:07,200
I want everything
here in 30 minutes!

388
00:24:08,233 --> 00:24:10,800
No problem, Hazel.

389
00:24:10,933 --> 00:24:15,800
All I ask is to release Felma.

390
00:24:23,300 --> 00:24:27,400
I'm giving you a way out.
A clean break.

391
00:24:27,533 --> 00:24:32,300
I promise you,
no one will know where you go.

392
00:24:32,467 --> 00:24:35,100
I'll talk to Manuel.
Bring him up here.

393
00:24:35,233 --> 00:24:36,833
Hazel, I'm the one you want,
right?

394
00:24:36,967 --> 00:24:39,667
Take it out on me.
Let Felma go!

395
00:24:42,333 --> 00:24:43,767
Hazel.

396
00:24:43,900 --> 00:24:45,367
That's enough.

397
00:24:46,733 --> 00:24:48,300
Target acquired.
